org.matsim.core.router

Class TripRouter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.core.router.TripRouter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MatsimExtensionPoint

    public final class TripRouter
extends Object
implements MatsimExtensionPoint
    Class acting as an intermediate between clients needing to compute routes and all registered RoutingModules. It provides convenience methods to route an individual trip with a desired mode or to identify trips.

    See tutorial.programming.ownMobsimAgentUsingRouter.RunOwnMobsimAgentUsingRouterExample for an example how to use this API from your own code. See tutorial.programming.example12PluggableTripRouter.RunPluggableTripRouterExample and tutorial.programming.example13MultiStageTripRouting.RunTeleportationMobsimWithCustomRoutingExample for examples how to extend or replace this behavior with your own.
    Author:
    thibautd

      • calcRoute

        public List<? extends PlanElement> calcRoute(String mainMode,
                                             Facility fromFacility,
                                             Facility toFacility,
                                             double departureTime,
                                             Person person)
        Routes a trip between the given O/D pair, with the given main mode.
        Parameters:
        mainMode - the main mode for the trip
        fromFacility - a Facility representing the departure location
        toFacility - a Facility representing the arrival location
        departureTime - the departure time
        person - the Person to route
        Returns:
        a list of PlanElement, in proper order, representing the trip.
        Throws:
        TripRouter.UnknownModeException - if no RoutingModule is registered for the given mode.

      • insertTrip

        public static List<PlanElement> insertTrip(Plan plan,
                                           Activity origin,
                                           List<? extends PlanElement> trip,
                                           Activity destination)
        Inserts a trip between two activities in the sequence of plan elements returned by the Plan.getPlanElements() method of a plan. Note that the plan will be modified only if the returned list is the internal reference!

        Note that this methods returns a unique solution because it expects the activity object references as arguments, which are unique.
        Parameters:
        plan - the plan to modify
        origin - the activity to use as origin. It must be a member of the list of plan elements.
        trip - the trip to insert
        destination - the destination activity. It must be a member of the list.
        Returns:
        the "old trip": the sequence of plan elements originally existing between the origin and the destination
